tspan.tspan: Divide the place notation (in column pn) of the parent method into places up to and including the mode,
and places above the mode. These places are entered in the columns headed <=m and >m respectively.
To obtain the the first extension (which is two stages higher), leave the places in column <=m unchanged, and increase
the places in column >m by two.
Then recombine the places in column <=m and column >m to obtain the place notation for the extended method.
The above can be repeated to obtain additional extensions in steps of 2 stages.
